us: “hole in the wall” references an obscure gathering location, possibly relating to the spoon, the red rooster, or an entirely different place. the episode will most likely be place-centric, with several scenes occurring at the same location. the term also refers to a place that is a secret, known to only a select few. this idea allows for one or more of the pairings on the show to find a special spot for themselves, which may lead to drama either between the couple themselves or the other people in the show. the title could also be talking about amber’s employment at the spoon, which is tied to TJ’s employment at the gym, possibly referencing the Kippen siblings. for certain, Cece and Ham’s relationship will be featured heavily in this episode, with possible references to a place they visited as young adults. and of course Bex and Bowie will have either nostalgic or tense moments regarding the so-called “hole in the wall”
